"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-johnmariani-2024-07-16-le-grand-colbert-is-a-secluded-and-very-romantic-restaurant-away-from-the-olympic-frenzy-in-paris\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByJohn Mariani, Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 29, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariani_Assembly_constituency\", \"score\": 0.9999889615928499, \"rank\": 1.103851900133756e-05, \"text\": \"Mariani\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariani_Assembly_constituency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariani_Assembly_constituency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contributor\", \"from\": 16, \"to\": 27}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other night my wife and I settled in to watch the 2003 Jack Nicholson-Diane Keaton rom-comSomething's Gotta Give, whose ending takes place at a brasserie named Le Grand Colbert on a rare night when it is snowing in Paris.\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 90, \"end\": 94, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9333663904595983, \"rank\": 0.07135628268584736, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}, {\"begin\": 251, \"end\": 256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0946382393345734e-34, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my wife\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 54}, {\"ngram\": \"whose ending\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 161}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 168, \"to\": 173}, {\"ngram\": \"a brasserie\", \"from\": 177, \"to\": 188}, {\"ngram\": \"Le Grand Colbert\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 211}, {\"ngram\": \"a rare night\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The movie is as delightful as ever and it reminded me of how romantic-and how very good-Colbert still is.\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 363, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The movie\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 267}, {\"ngram\": \"very good-Colbert\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who have never set foot in Colbert sniff that the movie made it into a tourist trap, and the management makes no secret of its association.\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2944574184825596e-11, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"foot\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"the movie\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 426}, {\"ngram\": \"a tourist trap\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"the management\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"no secret\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 490}, {\"ngram\": \"its association\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this is one of the city's classic brasseries, and its primary clientele are Parisian-most of them from the Second Arrondissement, just around the corner from the beautiful Jardin du Palais Royal and near the Bourse.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2nd_arrondissement_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Second Arrondissement\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2nd_arrondissement_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2nd_arrondissement_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 697, \"end\": 709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palais-Royal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0826072006804956e-57, \"text\": \"Palais Royal\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palais-Royal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palais-Royal\"}, {\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronext_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.698093248816553e-18, \"text\": \"Bourse\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronext_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronext_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city's classic brasseries\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 559}, {\"ngram\": \"its primary clientele\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"the corner\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1828 the Gallerie Colbert, named after Jean-Baptiste Colbert, minister for Louis XIV, opened and within was a novelty store calledAu Grand Colbert.But it wasn't until 1900 that it opened as a restaurant and for 85 years was under the same ownership, until taken over by theBibliotheque Nationale de France.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2944574184825596e-11, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}, {\"begin\": 776, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.223369639202449e-42, \"text\": \"Jean-Baptiste Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}, {\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"score\": 0.9999999690599002, \"rank\": 3.0939929682098525e-08, \"text\": \"Louis XIV\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.421583135897225e-18, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"minister\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"a novelty store calledAu Grand Colbert\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"a restaurant\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"85 years\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"the same ownership\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today the premises have national landmark status, and you will see why as soon as you enter in the glory of impeccably preserved art nouveau premises with tall mirrors,fin-de-sieclemurals, zinc bar, brass railings, bentwood chairs, shiny silverware, starched linens, gorgeous mosaic tile floors and effusions of green plants.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the premises\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"national landmark status\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"the glory\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"impeccably preserved art nouveau premises\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"tall mirrors\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1212}, {\"ngram\": \"fin\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"de\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"sieclemurals\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"zinc bar\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"brass railings\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"chairs\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"shiny silverware\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"starched linens\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"gorgeous mosaic tile floors\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"effusions\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"green plants\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its current owners took over in 1992 and polished everything to a bright sheen.\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its current owners\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"a bright sheen\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The menu seeks to break no culinary ground, although it is \\\"vegetarian friendly\\\" and offers gluten-free dishes.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1563, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The menu\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"no culinary ground\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"gluten-free dishes\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aside from a la carte, there is a very well-priced Le Bistrot menu at \\u20ac29 for three courses, and a Menu Parisian for \\u20ac55 for three courses.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1703, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a la carte\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"a very well-priced Le Bistrot menu\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"three courses\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"a Menu Parisian\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"three courses\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(The nice things about Colbert's website is that many of its dishes have accompanying photographs to stir your appetite.)\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2944574184825596e-11, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The nice things\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"its dishes\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1771}, {\"ngram\": \"accompanying photographs\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"your appetite\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last time I visited Colbert I was with my son, then about thirty years old, both of us just off a flight from New York, jetlagged and in need of sustenance.\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1851, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2944574184825596e-11, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}, {\"begin\": 1941, \"end\": 1949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999700617086, \"rank\": 2.993844224965343e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my son\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"a flight\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"need\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"sustenance\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We walked through the Jardin and there, as always, with its tall windows and red velvet curtains, its ancient door opening onto that glorious brasserie setting.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Jardin\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"its tall windows\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"red velvet curtains\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"its ancient door\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2102}, {\"ngram\": \"that glorious brasserie setting\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2147}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was early but guests began arriving by one o'clock, many greeted by name.\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2225, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"guests\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2172}, {\"ngram\": \"one o'clock\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2202}, {\"ngram\": \"name\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We, unknown, were treated just as cordially, despite our fumbled attempts at speaking French.\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2312, \"end\": 2318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7953303245877047, \"rank\": 0.25733920747733363, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our fumbled attempts\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's customary to begin with shellfish at a brasserie, and Colbert has a large selection, with six oysters (at dinner \\u20ac23-30, cheaper at lunch), an assiette of shellfish (\\u20ac38 ) and the Grand Colbert Royale with half a lobster and shellfish (\\u20ac83).\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2380, \"end\": 2387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2944574184825596e-11, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}, {\"begin\": 2512, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2944574184825596e-11, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Colbert\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"shellfish\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"a brasserie\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"a large selection\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"six oysters\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2427}, {\"ngram\": \"dinner\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2438}, {\"ngram\": \"lunch\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2463}, {\"ngram\": \"an assiette\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"shellfish\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"half a lobster\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Individual species are also available.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2606, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Individual species\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are a dozen or so appetizers, each perfected over decades, like frogs' legs a la Proven\\u00e7ale (\\u20ac25), a terrine of foie gras of duck (\\u20ac28) and of course onion soup gratin\\u00e9e (\\u20ac14).\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2726, \"end\": 2735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foie_gras\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.490457870590753e-78, \"text\": \"foie gras\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foie_gras\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foie_gras\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a dozen or so appetizers\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"frogs' legs\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"a la Proven\\u00e7ale\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2705}, {\"ngram\": \"a terrine\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"duck\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2743}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is even a plate of burrata and roasted tomatoes (\\u20ac23).\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 2851, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even a plate\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2812}, {\"ngram\": \"burrata\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2823}, {\"ngram\": \"roasted tomatoes\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next come the fish: sole meuni\\u00e8re (\\u20ac75), daurade royale with saffron sauce and vegetables (\\u20ac42), and that wonderful throwback of dauntingly rich quenelles of pike with lobster sauce and basmati rice (\\u20ac29).\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 3058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fish\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2871}, {\"ngram\": \"sole meuni\\u00e8re\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2886}, {\"ngram\": \"daurade royale\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2908}, {\"ngram\": \"saffron sauce\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2927}, {\"ngram\": \"vegetables\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2942}, {\"ngram\": \"that wonderful throwback\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"dauntingly rich quenelles\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3007}, {\"ngram\": \"pike\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3015}, {\"ngram\": \"lobster sauce\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3034}, {\"ngram\": \"basmati rice\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If it's meat you are after, there is a chateaubriand for two with Bearnaise and frites (\\u20ac98),boudin noirwith onions (\\u20ac28) and, to shown they are up to date, linguine with truffle cream (\\u20ac30).\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3251, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"meat\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"a chateaubriand\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3112}, {\"ngram\": \"Bearnaise\", \"from\": 3126, \"to\": 3135}, {\"ngram\": \"frites\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u20ac98),boudin noirwith onions\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3175}, {\"ngram\": \"date\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3215}, {\"ngram\": \"truffle crea